text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. ***
time is running out!!!!!!
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (linktree in bio to sign up) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!

text:
6 months ago today i was assaulted. and i'm angry. i'm angry it happened. i'm angry that i now see the world as a before and after. i had 22 years before an assault and now it's the after. i'm angry that i call it 'the thing' instead of an assault which it actually was; trivialising myself so people don't try to do it for me.

i'm angry that i blame myself. i'm a feminist and i know about the culture that exists. my dissertation surrounded the topic of rape culture and feminism. and yet, here i am, still thinking that it was me, because that's what the media and culture tell us. i'm angry it's like this. 
and maybe 6 months isn't enough time to process it? i don't want to be angry forever, and i don't think i will. i want to be hopeful; hopeful i can use this anger for something positive. i'm really fucking hopeful that our culture does start to change and that shit like this won't happen. .
.
.
.
#metoo #feminism #feminist #imfedup

text:
so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show. 
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement, which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist, carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.
the hypocrisy of hollywood, which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades â€” all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

carter was the symbol for female power of her time ğŸ’ªğŸ½
on the very set of wonder woman, for instance, she said she discovered that a cameraman had drilled a hole into her dressing room. 
she said that watching the #metoo movement develop had been emotional and moving for her, and that she hoped lasting change would flow from it, â€œthough i think itâ€™s regional. often in red states you find racism, and where you find racism you also find sexism.â€ #wonderwoman #sexism #smashthepatriarchy #hollywood #lyndacarter #streetart #wonderwomanstreetart #art #instaart #spraypaint #freehand #femaleempowerment #femaleicons #hypocriticalhollywood #sexualabuse #superhero #women

text:
so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show. 
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement, which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist, carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.
the hypocrisy of hollywood, which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades â€” all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

carter was the symbol for female power of her time ğŸ’ªğŸ½
on the very set of wonder woman, for instance, she said she discovered that a cameraman had drilled a hole into her dressing room. 
she said that watching the #metoo movement develop had been emotional and moving for her, and that she hoped lasting change would flow from it, â€œthough i think itâ€™s regional. often in red states you find racism, and where you find racism you also find sexism.â€ #wonderwoman #sexism #smashthepatriarchy #hollywood #lyndacarter #streetart #wonderwomanstreetart #art #instaart #spraypaint #freehand #femaleempowerment #femaleicons #hypocriticalhollywood #sexualabuse #superhero #women

-

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the effos made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to cou documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

text:
here are some options for at-home protein treatments for hair:

egg mask.

you can make a protein treatment for natural hair with eggs you have at home. eggs are probably the best protein treatment for heat damaged natural hair because they are rich not only in protein, but in beneficial enzymes. egg is a good natural protein treatment for damaged hair because hair that has been treated via heat or product tends to be very brittle and very dry. for a protein treatment for natural fine hair, use the entire egg. beat until frothy and apply evenly to hair and scalp, cover with a cap or warm towel, and let mixture sit for 20 minutes. for a natural protein treatment for frizzy hair or oily hair, use only the egg whites. this egg protein treatment for natural hair can be used as an at-home protein treatment for hair every two weeks or on a monthly basis.

yogurt.
yogurt, sour cream and similar dairy products contain not only protein, but lactic acid, which cleanses your hair while the fat in the dairy moisturizes it. this is a great weekly treatment that will revitalize and bring luster back to your hair. to create an extra powerful homemade protein conditioner, add an egg into your yogurt mixture. let your mixture sit for up to 20 minutes before washing out.

avocado.
for powerful results, try a protein treatment for natural hair with avocado. avocados are not only loaded with protein and nutrients, but their high-fat content has great benefits when applied to hair. avocados repair hair damage, strengthen hair strands, and make hair less dry, brittle and prone to breakage. mix half of a smashed up avocado with 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise (which contains egg protein) and apply this homemade protein conditioner to your hair weekly.

coconut oil.
coconut oil or coconut butter is rich in healthy fats and proteins that are great as a natural protein treatment for damaged hair. applying a mask of coconut oil to your hair can provide a very economical, deep-moisturizing treatment that can give you great results.

text:
yesterday, i went to my first gymnastics meet as a coach! ğŸ˜­ growing up, i was a competitive gymnast. both in childhood and later in life, this sport has made tremendous impact on my life. it has taught me how to be fierce, brave, strong, independent, confident, and it gave me an insatiable work ethic!
. 
gymnastics is not just a sport of the body. more than anything, gymnastics is a sport of the mind. it will bring you face to face with things that scare you the shit out of you and it will reward you for facing them by showing you that you are capable of literally anything that you allow your energy to flow into.
. 
moving my body has always been necessary to reach beyond the mental and emotional blocks standing in my way. not only is it a relief to step away from the energy of blocks, but it is truly miraculous and healing to transmute those blocks.
. 
i see everything in my life as divine. it's no accident i grew up a gymnast. it's no accident that i take great honor and respect for my role as a gymnastics coach now. it's no accident that this sport has moulded me as a person and that it continues to do so.
. 
i was born for this.
. 
the world of gymnastics is admist an incredible transformation. the collective athletic soul of this nation is healing. ğŸ™ if you were, or currently are a gymnast who has experienced a trauma in your sport such as injury, emotional or sexual abuse, or mental blocks keeping you from your higher level skills, then i would love for you to reach out to me. we just might be soul mates! ğŸ’• i am here to help you uncover your emotional traumas, and be a supportive guide in your healing.
. 
your story has been no accident either. you were born to change the world and i truly believe you will. i love you! ğŸ’“
.

please follow the link in my bio to reach out to me. ğŸ˜˜

text: for this episode, we wanted to help support survivors whose stories are, unfortunately, far too commonplace to be featured on our show. to that end, we are featuring @safe_alliance as our cause of the week. check out their page to get an idea of the important work they do! according to research presented by safealliance.org, 1-in-3 women will be impacted by sexual assault or domestic violence during their life time. three women are killed each day in the usa by an intimate partner. every 2 minutes someone in the usa is sexually assaulted. one in every 4 girls, and 1 in every 6 boys will be sexually assaulted before their 18th birthday. if you are as horrified by these statistics as we are, please join us in supporting the cause. you can donate directly on their site safealliance.org, or you can support us on patreon, where 100% of donations beyond our minimal operating costs will be funneled to a new causes like this one each week. https://www.patreon.com/stftalk. thank you!

text:
good morning and happy monday!  todayâ€™s challenge ~ name one thing you like about yourself ... now name one more!
.
how did you do with that?  was it easy to identify 2 things you like about yourself?  or did it take you a bit of time?  being able to identify our positives, our strengths and to like ourselves is part of improving our self-worth. .
if you want to take this challenge to the next level, make a list of 50 things you like about yourself.  50, you ask?! yep, 50.  now, the â€œrulesâ€ to this challenge is to do it yourself â€” donâ€™t ask those around you what they like about you and donâ€™t use a thesaurus.  the goal is to improve your self-worth. if you ask others, and you get upset with that person you will discount what they say.  if we do this ourselves, it will mean more. ğŸ’œ

text:
i invited people from my father's acquaintance,
at the orix theater
i have seen something rotten.

it seems that in 2015 the tony award at the broadway was also awarded with a supporting actor award.
i remembered it at the theater.
as i was in my second year of junior high school around 2000, 
because nobody speaks,
 i was losing something from my desk at the school just before i was writing lyrics.
by the way it seems that there was also an adult actress with the same name as me.
as a classmate, there is a girl who is yukiko fuyama with her childhood friend at that time, well
"in the future, it seems to be an adult actress"
i was told.
by the way the father worked for an advertising company and someone later taught me that such a person with the same name as me was truly back then.
actually, i started from an elementary school before this.

text:
pmsÂ stands for premenstrual syndrome â€“ it's the combination of symptoms that some women suffer from a week or so before their period. symptoms appear before your period starts (as many as five days) and will disappear during your period. pmsÂ is a group of changes that can affect you on many levels and varies person to person. they can be physical, emotional, or behavioral.

physical signs
-weight gain
-cramps
-swollen hands and feet
-bloated tummy
-tender breast
-pimples
-hunger
-constipation or diarrhea

emotional signs
-mood swings
-tense or anxious
-angry outbursts
-don't want to be with people
-feel overwhelmed or out of control
-can't sleep
-crying

behavioral signs
-forget things
-loss of mental focus
-tired
.
.

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnâ€™s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganâ€™s app may not have been completely deleted. koganâ€™s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
(1/3) "in the fruit of our womb, christina is given a chance at a new life with a wealthy manhattan couple who decide to adopt her. their intentions seem beyond reproach. but what starts off as a perfect utopian family, quickly turns into a nightmare.
while doing research for the film, i came across some staggering statistics. it became clear that child sex abuse (especially in foster families) is much more common than we allow ourselves to believe. 
obviously, not all of these people are clinical diagnosed as mentally ill, the majority are ordinary citizens that live according to societal rules. if they are extreme in anything, itâ€™s their conformity. and yet they cross over to the territory of â€œthe unthinkableâ€ with such ease. they must find a way to normalize it somehow â€“ at least to themselves."
stay tuned this week and next as we share more comments from director marina shron about the process of researching & writing #thefruitofourwomb
#tfoow #ourwomb

text:
what is the sexual harassment case against rajkumar hirani ? 
in an email dated november 3, 2018, a woman accused director rajkumar hirani of sexual harassment. the email was addressed to hirani's frequent collaborator vidhu vinod chopra, his wife anupama chopra, scriptwriter abhijat joshi and shelly chopra dhar, who is the director of 'ek ladki ko dekha toh aisa laga' and also vinod chopra's sister. 
the complainant was working as hirani's assistant for the film 'sanju', during which the alleged incident took place. according to the email, the complainant was harassed from march to september 2018. 
#metoo #asiaville

text:
me too movement...
.
.
the #metoo movement is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault. .
.  origin 
the phrase #metoo was coined by tarana burke in 2006 as part of a campaign to promote "empowerment through empathy" among women of color who have experienced sexual abuse, particularly within underprivileged communities.
.
.  popular...
fast forward to 2017, #metoo became viral on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplace. it followed soon afterÂ the sexual abuse allegations againstÂ a high profile celebrity. .
.  properly defined...
creatorÂ tarana burkeÂ is quite specific about the  goals for the #metoo movement which includes..
1# processing all untested rape kits in the united states,

2# investigating the vetting of teachers.

3# better protecting children at school.

4# updating sexual harassment policies, and improving training in workplaces, places of worship, and schools. .
.
everyone in a community, including men and women, must take action in order to make the #metoo movement a success. .
.

text:
tw//:vegan/food (tw is for anyone who has a ed or doesn't want to hear about me being vegan fyi)
.
.
i made the decision about a week ago to go vegan. i decided this for myself, and i would never try to guilt my partners, or others to go vegan. -
i made this decision because i am autistic (autism spectrum disorder), and sensory issues go with that, especially around food. i relied on meat, dairy, any other animal products to give me all my nutrients. when they couldn't possibly give me those. - 
i don't want people to think that going vegan solves sensory issues. i don't want you guys to think i am saying that. it has been very hard. yet 100% worth it. it causes me to get up, prepare my food, write down what i like, what i don't like. do research around what to substitute! know what i need to eat to get the right amount of protein, and other nutrients. -
for me going vegan was 100% worth it. it was also a big factor of knowing what was going into my body, and has helped me recover from sexual abuse. again, going vegan isn't for everyone, but i have noticed that my body functions better, my tummy is happier, my brain is operating faster, my mental health has improved (some), and feelings around/about food has improved!
food:
1 cup of almond milk 
1 apple cinnamon rice cake 
1 sliced banana 
1/4 cup of peanutbutter

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this 10 year throwback challenge has really weighed heavy on my heart and my mind. and my reasoning for posting this is that maybe there are some women out there going through the same thing.
alot of people didnt know that 10 years ago i was in an incredibly abusive relationship. not only physical, spiritual, emotional... it nearly killed me. i could write a book on my year experience with him!
glow up is one thing..and lordt i know my glow up is real ğŸ˜‚
the photo on the left were photos i had to ask my mum to take of me. can you imagine asking your mum to take photos of your bruises?? i can only thank god i made it out alive and for all the blessings i have received. 
i am stronger than ever. i have 2 beautiful children. a wonderful husband.
he is still out there. and im still standing. 
if you are going through the same thing please feel free to message me. you are stronger than you know. god has your back. #survivor #abusesurvivor #metoo #strongwomen

the photo on the left were photos i had to ask my mum to take of me. can you imagine asking your mum to take photos of your bruises?? i can only thank god i made it out alive and for all the blessings i have received. 
i am stronger than ever. i have 2 beautiful children. a wonderful husband.
he is still out there. and im still standing. 
if you are going through the same thing please feel free to message me. you are stronger than you know. god has your back.

kali
it was my motherâ€™s fault that she birthed
me on the banks of kaveri
for try as they did they could not wash the black alluvial soil off my skin

kali
this one just got baked a little longer in the oven laughs my father when
my mother guiltily presents him with yet another daughter
one whose skin only a paddy farmer could love.

kali
i am six when i am made to understand that
i who was proudly showing off my 99% in maths was less than my classmate,
at least iâ€™m fairer than you she says,
sadly looking down at her own 73% marks

kali
the shame i feel looking at my white face black neck makeup at my arangetram
the shame
is for the secret pleasure that even though i look like a clown, i am fair
for two hours

kali
i burn my skin to a crisp with hydrogen peroxide, congratulations.
i now possess blonde sideburns to contrast my black skin.

kali
the proud mother of a prospective groom, who insisted on a fair skinned bride
for her son who was â€˜white as milkâ€™
amma told her off in no uncertain terms that her daughter
is dark as decoction and only when you mix the two.
do you get rich aromatic
coffee

the boy who said your skin shines
like burnished copper.
i let him go, i thought he was lying.
boris becker declared that the only time
he noticed that his girlfriend was black
was when he saw how beautiful her skin
looked against his white sheets

wondering how he could find me desirable

text:
life is dangerous. some of our most harrowing experiences have happened outside of the bush. let me tell you about this one. i was sure we were going to die...for about 10 seconds. spoiler: we didnâ€™t.  it was just before christmas. misty and i had driven to anchorage. the best shopping happens in anchorage. we had some capital in our possession. naturally, we needed to spend it. it was a good night. we stacked deep in business supplies and picked up a few more gifts for the overly spoiled childs. i even picked up two sport coats. you canâ€™t be a professional without looking good. thatâ€™s why iâ€™m still an amateur.
we finished up our shopping and headed home. our little toyota corolla was packed floor to ceiling. my hat and face mask were stuffed in the far back corner of the rear windshield. more on that later. i had a new laptop, a new camcorder, some new software, a ton of leather, and my two fancy sport coats all in the backseat. weâ€™d had a good night. 
we were driving along, discussing our lives and our future. we were making plans and talking about strategies. we talked about the kids. â€œi think iâ€™m going to introduce ella to star wars.â€ i knew she would love it. something we could bond over. i had made a promise to god almighty at her birth (another story). star wars wasnâ€™t in it. iâ€™ll explain that later. i donâ€™t care much who understands it.
weâ€™re driving along. i mentioned the book â€œhow to win friends and influence peopleâ€. i never did read that book. the road was clear of snow, but had an icy sheen on it. it was cold that night. the road was black. the night was dark. there was no other traffic.
â€œmoose!â€ misty shouted frantically. there was no moose on the road, and then there was. it was standing broadside. itâ€™s hide was a perfect match for the black road and the black night. no eye shine. it just appeared in front of us. too late to do anything. it was standing directly in our lane. my first reaction was a no no. i slammed on the breaks. my second reaction was a no no. i cut my wheel to the left. at that point i remembered my first mistake and pumped the break so as not to spin us out of control. didnâ€™t matter. cont in comments â¬‡ï¸

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

text:
women are changing. i've been noticing it for a while. with a passionate side hustle, a strong independent decision, a push through the glass ceiling....little signs that pop up to show me â¡ï¸women everywhere are changing. ğŸ’•we are becoming more alive, embracing our freedom that has been so deeply fought for by those before us.ğŸ’• we've seen in the #metoo movement, in #heforshe , in the #gendergap fight. ğŸ˜‡ women are stepping into their place. â¡ï¸ and for the first time in my life, this summer, i have seen it all around me as i take adventures with my kids. the women at the pool are confidently wearing their bathers, not covering themselves out of insecurity ğŸ‘™ the mothers are walking their prams in the evenings, wearing their tiny shorts & fitted tanks. ğŸƒâ€â™€ï¸ the 60 year old life-long friends having coffee together, are wearing mini skirts & body cons â˜• women are loving themselves more, loving their bodies more. we are saying #effyourbeautystandards and actually meaning it. ğŸ’• the message of self love and confidence is getting through. it's changing us.  after a lifetime of feeling the pain of women hating themselves, of fighting that myself, of watching my mother cover herself and my friends mock their 'mum bodies', there is finally a light ğŸŒŸ i, for one, am so bloody glad to see it. not just for the freedom it brings the rest of my life, but because the future i want for my daughter is now becoming possible. ğŸ˜ she can feel confident in her body, every day. she can feel freedom in what she wears, every day. she can be courageous in pursuing what sets her soul on fire, every day. she can stand on the shoulders of women who have fought to create this life, and feel the exhilaration of a life wide open, with anything possible, every day. ğŸ’• all because we started believing we could wear tiny clothes without shame. so go for the bikinis, ladies. go for the tiny skirts, the low cut tee, the fitted jeans..go for what makes you feel confident and sexy af, because you're not just doing it for you..you're doing it for our daughters.

text:
iâ€™ve had a troubling week inside my noggin. many intrusive thoughts, lots of mini-flashbacks, lots of thoughts of the assault and any and all events linked to it from getting overly drunk with my ex and ex flatmate to crying on my own in woodford and receiving a vicious note from one of my flatmates essentially telling me to stfu or else, missing london yet not feeling a great sense of warmth for wanting to ever go back, anxiety, depression and massive sleeping problems from insomnia to oversleeping. i even caught myself scratching at my arms which i havenâ€™t done in a couple of months now. 
iâ€™m about to get my clean on and am at peace that if i need to get obsessive with it, itâ€™s more than allowed and is one of my coping mechanisms as long as i see it that way.
iâ€™m very self aware and aware that i am not screwing things up but feel like i am, constantly.
i saw a great post earlier this morning that, in a nutshell, read:
stop making people with mental health problems feel bad for their symptoms...we overthink, overcompensate, are sorry and are trying. 
iâ€™m trying. iâ€™m just not sure if itâ€™s enough for anyone else but me and my little man.

text:
in case you needed a reason to move to hawaii... on january 1, 2019 at the stroke of midnight, hawaii joined california and a few municipalities in new york to ban prospective employers from asking applicants about their prior salary history.  jurisdictions that have already passed similar laws that place restrictions on salary history during the application process include california, new york city, westchester, and suffolk county, new york. 
the new law, senate bill 2351, was signed by governor david y. ige on july 5, 2018. the relevant section states, in part, that â€œthe legislature believes that the ability of employers to consider a job applicantâ€™s previous salary history is a contributing factor to the gender pay disparity.â€ the section further cites new york cityâ€™s 2017 passage of similar legislation as a model to follow to â€œpromote equality in the workplace and [to] close the pay gap between men and women.â€ read the full article here:  https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/new-year-new-law-hawaii-s-ban-on-prior-83796/  #womeninsurfing #womengetpaid #womeninsports #nastywomen #genderequality #metoo #timesup #womensmarch #womenvote #womenswave #whyimarch #imarchfor #equality #womensrights #feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #futureisfemale #femaleempowerment #girlsrule #girlsruntheworld #girlboss #ladyboss #ovarygang #girlpower #grlpower #womensupportingwomen #surfergirl #surfergrl

text:
people are outraged about this picture because you don't get to opt in and out of activism because you wanted to be 'nice'. the point of activism is that you stand your ground, even when it's uncomfortable.

in her case, she gets paid for this shit then she must be willing to do the work required. she did a whole cover last year for cosmo where she was branded as an 'activist', so people have a right to be pissed off when she pulls a stunt like this (taking a picture with an alleged abuser), especially now with theÂ #muteÂ campaign in the air. we don't only get to choose who is outraged by (#survivingrkelly) as though there are predators around us that we protect.  also, she didn't say she was afraid to say no. had the photo not been on online or had people not been outraged by its existence, would she have 'cringed' with the people? the 'apology' seems more like damage control/pr to protect her beloved 'good girl' brand than anything else. "the only thing necessary for the triumph of evil is for good men to do nothing" edmund burke. there is a place for 'niceness', playing nice with an alleged abuser isn't one of those moments. she committed to speak for and represent people who can't do those things for themselves, you don't get to take that hat off when it suits you, its a fucking full-time job. as an activist, she needs to uphold that commitment in almost all aspects of her life (private and public). you need to pick a side and commit to it. 
#metoo #timesup #survivingarthur
#wokeproject
name: Rebone Masemola

text:
my friend sexually assaulted me one year ago this weekend. it was the most horrific moment of my life, creating the most horrifying and darkest year i have ever lived. and in all that horror, i choose to celebrate the gift that i was given as a result of the trauma. 
i write this letter to you. 
you stripped me down to nothing but a lifeless, soulless, empty vessel, but somehow my heart remained beating, it was a shallow beat, but it was there. 
through your inconceivable action when you felt that you love and adored me and wanted every piece of me, without my permission, in a snap of fingers, poof, goodbye jennalee. but my heart remained beating. 
i couldnâ€™t feel, i couldnâ€™t smile, i couldnâ€™t touch or be touched, and this went on and on and on, but my heart remained beating. 
when i had multiple breakdowns and ended up on medication, contemplated at least 5 times or more over the first 7 mths, if i should continue to live or not, somehow my heart remained beating. 
when adam would remind me he was there for me in whatever way i needed, no matter what was happing in our world, my heart would beat a little more. 
when i drank night after night for months on end so i could laugh and feel free, happy and normal, but would often cry in a bathroom as all the personal judgment came flowing at me, if i didnâ€™t pass out first, my heart remained beating, even if it didnâ€™t want to. 
when my little girls smiled at me and told me how much they loved me and missed me, and didnâ€™t want me to be sick anymore, my heart would beat a little stronger. 
and then when i would be triggered and reminded of what you did to me, it would slow again, but it remained beating. 
i lost people in my life that didnâ€™t understand the way i was now or didnâ€™t know how to be around me, it was okay, i understood, my heart remained beating. 
with each new beautiful soul that came into my life, and accepted me as i was, my heart beat even more. 
and with each time over the year i was triggered my heart remained beating, and with each beat it would get stronger and stronger. i told you, you could not bury me alive. my seed had been planted and that i wold grow into a big oak tree. 
more below...

text_retweet: this is a repost from amplifier. representation matters. representing our loved ones, representing humanity. representing our strength in acknowledging eachother as humans with eachother, and with our own lives to return to. that's who we are. when overexposure, exploitation, or force against natural will is inflicted, it's disgusting. how could you not notice the being with thumbs, working hands, ridiculously shiny knee caps,  just like yours or anyone you consider close too. our country has looked many ways to the world for longer than these last two years. presentation is different. our lives are not a feature. not a political front or game. i do try to be part in activism, though activism is very much about representation, not an expensive campaign to present. not an elaborate fancy fixture, devaluing life, pretentiously expecting the real people with actual issues, maybe health problems, maybe any genuine humanity to be cast out, because they simply aren't wearing a sweater approved of. representation, is the priceless value of speaking and working for the betterment and future of life itself to continue to gain understanding, and being straight with eachother, not needing approval, to try, to see eachother; as we are.  knowing ourselves, eachother, our world, respecting boundaries and limits without forcing beliefs to degrade freedoms of the whole jam. it's inhibiting, and rude habitat to base opinion, judgement, critique, and depleat resources to continue to degrade people equally human, if not sometimes actually more humane to others, for how they were born naturally. in the movement, i respect lgbt, maybe you were born that way, i don't expect you to change. it's cool, your rights matter. your right to love is right. i personally consider the rights to live and breathe, a better place to start. that's how i see it, start with a solid base, on children, women and minorities, accomplish and push for rights to love. its important, although, that's how you present yourself, and represent how you prefer to be loved, that's not a priority over representing lives. maybe help get active in ours too. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #lgbtq

text:
protein treatments are designed to create a protective barrier for your hair. the additional proteins grab onto the hair follicle and fill any holes or gaps within the cuticle.

the result is stronger hair that has an extra layer of protection from damaging elements. it also looks and feels healthier.

it is only a temporary fix, however. that is why regular protein treatments are recommended, though it's also important not to go overboard. when paired with deep conditioning, the protein treatments can become an important part of maintaining or restoring healthy hair.

protein treatments do help maintain strong tresses, but they should be used sparingly. the ingredients that strengthen your hair and fill in cuticle gaps can also dry it out. overdoing it on the proteinâ€”especially while not applying enough moisture in the form of regular, deep conditioningâ€”can lead to brittle hair.

you should always follow up protein treatments with moisturizing conditioners, preferably a deep conditioning treatment.

text:
"i am one"
today i looked in the mirror & reflected on all that i been through in life...from sexual abuse & rape, sickness, death, sleepless nights, worry, disappointments & so much more that i saw how each trial seem to separate me fom who i  really am...but when i looked closer i also saw that even though in this life i may have many trials & tribulations that as long as i keep my faith in christ jesus that still "i am one" in him.

text:
i've always been "small" or skinny. i never felt good in my body. always picked on for being too tall, or too lanky, ilooked like a praying mantis or a giraffe. my maternal grandfather and my sperm donor were both tall, thin men, its genetic obviously, and yet even my own "family" members have accused me of having a eating disorder. (first 2 pics)

2017 was probably the worst year of my life and i do not say that lightly. i was in an extremely unhealthy and unsafe relationship. i became someone i never wanted to be in order to survive. i did things i, as who i am in my heart, at my core, would never do. and yet, i was still on the verge of death. love can be so beautiful and warm, safe, fulfilling. but also be cold, hurtful, maddening and blinding. especially when its already isolated you from everyone and everything you love, everything that makes you, so beautifully you. and then you don't notice until it's too late.. or so you think. (next 2 pics was me when i walked away the first time)

2017 nearly killed me, but it also saved my life. it showed me that i needed 2 love myself. that i needed 2 accept myself. that i needed 2 respect myself. i couldn't look myself in the mirror and say "i love you"...today i feel the most absolute best in my body n about who i am, than i have ever felt before! i feel confident and healthy. i am confident and healthy! my sexiness, my womanness can only go up from here!! to the world i say this "to everyone who has ever felt like they were in the wrong body, that it didnt feel right to them, to every person who's ever been in an abusive or just unhealthy relationship and you dont see the way out, to every person who's ever been ashamed of who you are... you are beautiful! every scar, every mole, every curve, every type of hair, every skin color, every gender, every sexual preference...you are beautiful in every aspect of you! believe in yourself. surround yourself with people who also believe in you so they can lift you up on those days you wanna give up. fuck it, reach out to me and i will build you up! i got you. because you got you! peace. love. and light sistahs and brothasâœŒğŸ¾ #selfcare #selflove #respect #believe #love

text:
the feelings get to you and change you. perception is altered and messes begin in places you never visit again. only memories stick and you wish you could erase the damage with a simple tearful blink. i have a home now. i am content in the warm glow that iâ€™ve created within my nest. while the worst has gripped me, i am able to release myself from its madness and leave it in the dirty, deep black blanket that covers the emptiness i hide from inside.

text:
watching ice cream melt, waiting for the children: more time to think. a summer's tale: chapter 6.
"shaz. can you get that bleeder for me."
it was surgery day for jerome, and there were 6 male cats waiting to be desexed.
"as i always say, 'you can't beat a castrated male as a perfect companion!'" sharon had an urge to stab him with the scalpel. she had heard this joke for mths and was over it. she was waiting for the reverse #metoo movement to start so she could secretly out him, but there didn't seem to be much interested.
"shaz. another bleed. grab it will you?. thanks." he dropped the severed testicle into the bin, and continued, "did you here bout the westies in the car with that dead fellow?" sharon was busy trying to work out where the sudden sea of blood was coming from. finally she located the bleeding vessel, clamped it off, and using a handful of guaze swabs removed the excess blood. the second testicle was now in plain view. "i read that there were 2 great danes in the car, and they were guarding the body," said sharon.
"i haven't read this morning news read. what else have they said?"
"they had trouble getting the body away from one of the dogs and had to shoot it..."
"they reported that in the news feed?"
"what?" sharon asked. "that they had to shoot the dog. i'm surprised the police released that bit of information "
"they didn't. the reporter quoted, 'unnamed sources.'"
"any comment from the police?"
"only 'no comment'" replied sharon
"they always close ranks when there is a shooting," commented jerome.
with that he felt his phone vibrate in his pocket.

who was trying to contact jerome? 
all will be revealed in the next chapter of 'a summer's tale'

text:
gratitude george, u r a life saver.
because of u my sweet dog, my tender constant companion, my canine love...
i am still alive.
the alpha of 2019 has been a colossal fiasco. my detested demon depression has reared its ugly head once again.
so here goes - a genesis of posts about my story. 
shall i call it â€œliving with a killer?â€ absolutely. because thats what it is!
the #1 cause of disability in the world is depression. 
suicide is the #2 cause of death in 15-29 year olds.
i know thereâ€™s a profound number of u out there who suffer from this dreadful illness. i vow to bare my soul so that others who r silently suffering will b heard. 
chances r, if u donâ€™t have it, 
u donâ€™t really get it.
chances r if u know someone w/it,
u understand it better, & chances r if youâ€™ve lost someone from suicide, 
u r traumatized, but still donâ€™t truly fathom why a person would choose to end their life.
(imagine depression as the pain of drowning in a scalding vat of boiling oil)
now is the time to explain wtf this demon does to a person from firsthand knowledge.
i hope to god this post makes whoever reads it more hopeful, understanding, & educated in something unthinkably heinous.
but most of all, to u in agony, u r not alone thinking about death as a way out. 
this candor may upset many people but thatâ€™s tough. iâ€™m writing this not to make friends, but to save lives!
my 1st piece of advice to my fellow depression brethren;
get as close to a dog as possible. if u r able to adopt a dog, run donâ€™t walk.... iâ€™m partial to dogs for depression, please no hate from cat lovers. i loved & had 7 cats at one time but they didnâ€™t help me as much as a 1 dog. 
i adopted george from @dogswithoutborders & think they 
r incredible af. 
please - if u can pick up the phone & call 1 person u suspect is sad/depressed then do it asap. better yet, if possible hug them.
i pray to god this reaches as many people as possible.
if u could post comments this would b incredibly appreciated.
with all the #love in my heart, & as much #hope as i can muster, carlye 
#depressionawareness #ptsd #sadness #understanding #suicideprevention #metoo #kindness #death #pain #pray 
#dogadoption #emotional #support

text:
i finished watching "surviving r. kelly". i was pretty young when allegations started coming out about r. kelly to really understand what was going on but i'm a grown woman now and i get it.
â€¢
â€¢
i understand that women of all races are affected by rape and mental and physical abuse including men but right now this is about a community of black girls and people are blaming them, calling them "fast girls", "where were there parents", "why are these girls not leaving" or still making jokes about this and flat out remaining to believe this man is innocent. that's your prerogative but it's also saying a big "fuck you" to these girls; it's like saying and i have heard from people point blank that it was these girls faults. do you know how it feels to be so scared of letting your family down, scared of the things these predators may go after your family or the humiliation and guilt you feel.
â€¢
â€¢
these girls were little girls and were brainwashed for years. so when people say "why did these women stay why did they not tell there parents or why didn't they go after r. kelly" first of all some of these girls did not have parents to defend them and brainwashing is a real thing. plus they were little girls! a grown man with all this money and fame promising young girls fame and fortune, only to be treated like animals, raped and abused and turned away from those who did have caring parents. my heart breaks for these girls/women and for the families involved and with out there daughters. i pray that some kind of justice is served for these victims/survivors and that maybe people will start listening and put this monster away so he can not ruin anymore lives.
â€¢
â€¢
#metoo #survingrkelly #muterkelly #fuckrkelly #survivor #rape #mentalillness #ptsd #westandtogether #protectblackwomen #rapeawareness #protectrapevictims #mentalhealth #stopvictimblaming

text:
bless the thing that broke you down and cracked you wide open, because the world needs you open. // rebecca campbell

everyone has that thing that broke you.  that thing that created a before and after.  that thing that has caused great suffering, yet has allowed you to heal in ways you never knew you were capable.  when we let go of that pain that has controlled us for so long, you begin to realize your strength even in all those raw and broken places.

you rise past it and you can live the life you deserve.

week two: yoga for depression

come join us in the third and final week, next sunday.  as we explore how to find compassion yourself through yoga.

www.swanriverarabi.com

text:
hot news
sutradara film sanju, rajkumar hirani tersandung masalah pelecehan seksual ğŸ˜¯

tahun 2019 tampaknya belum berakhir yang menyangkut terkait kasus pelecehan seksual. meskipun telah melihat cukup banyak nama yang diciptakan oleh gerakan #metoo, nama terbaru yakni pembuat film rajkumar hirani pasti mengejutkan satu bollywood. terlepas dari orang-orang di media sosial, selebritis seperti vinta nanda juga menyatakan ketidakpercayaannya pada pembuat film berkelas ini yang dituduh melakukan pelanggaran seksual. 
yang terakhir bereaksi sama adalah aktris amardeep jha. amardeep jha baru-baru ini membuka suara tentang pengalaman dirinya bekerja dengan rajkumar hirani. menurut laporan media, amardeep mengatakan bahwa di lokasi syuting, rajkumar hirani bahkan seperti malaikat berjalan. menurut apa yang amardeep ketahui tentang sang sutradara secara pribadi, berita ini pasti mengejutkan dia.

berbicara tentang tuduhan yang ditujukan kepada rajkumar hirani, mengatakan bahwa meskipun rajkumar tidak dapat menghakimi gadis itu, dia secara pribadi merasa bahwa rajkumar tidak dapat melakukan pelecehan itu. rajkumar bahkan tidak pernah memberikan komentar cabul atau membuat lelucon kasar di lokasi syuting.

menurut laporan media, asisten direktur rajkumar hirani dari film sanju telah menuduh pembuat film itu melakukan pelecehan seksual padanya lebih dari satu kali. wanita itu bahkan mengirim surat tentang hal yang sama kepada rajkumar hirani dan rekan-rekannya yang termasuk vidhu vinod chopra dan istrinya anupama chopra.

rajkumar hirani baru-baru ini merilis pernyataan yang menyangkal semua tuduhan yang ditujukan kepadanya. dia mengatakan dalam pernyataan itu, â€œsaya benar-benar terkejut ketika tuduhan ini diajukan kepada saya sekitar dua bulan yang lalu. saya segera menyarankan bahwa penting untuk membawa masalah ini ke komite atau badan hukum mana pun. pengadu memilih untuk pergi ke media sebagai gantinya. saya ingin menyatakan dengan sangat kuat bahwa ini adalah cerita jahat yang salah dan nakal yang disebarkan dengan tujuan menghancurkan reputasi sayaâ€. ğŸ˜¯

a series. .

away from me. -mahriyah willow

text:
words for the world:
me too part 7.
a series. .
.
.
sex loses meaning after each time. eventually, i believed each person was allowed to take from me what they wanted. i felt hurt and ugly when they did not 'want' me.
.
.
.
you make me laugh and 
seem so sweet.
you are being kind so - 
what do i have 
to offer you?
the same thing they all wanted...
.
.
yet now you say 
that i am too easy,
what is it then? 
am i a slut or 
am i a tease...
because they both 
make me feel
wrong. -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

.
.

text:
words for the world:
me too part 10.
a series. .
.
.
why you wanted me
i never knew
felt like i was broken
until you told me
hold your head up high
you are not your past
and we are going somewhere fast. .
.
.
gentle kisses on my forhead,
tender whispers in my ear.
with you i feel what i
have not felt before.
friendship first
and so much patience.
you saw me at my worst
before you ever got my best.
i know we are lucky
for having what we do,
that you have been through
so much too. 
thank you for 
never being mad 
that sometimes i shrink 
away from you,
fearing not you
but those that came before.
know that i appreciate
each time you wipe my tears
and assure me that 
one day i will feel 
like me again.
your love has been my
little caccoon -
keeping me warm during
my layers of healing. 
i can't wait till the day
my mind clears up
and my body trusts,
when it will be just
you and i.
â™¡â™¡ -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

text:
words for the world:
me too part 11.
a series. .
the end.. for now
.
ask yourself
"does this feel right?" if you get a pit
it most certainly isn't
.
maybe as we grow
we learn not everything 
can be defined by
the limited exposures 
of our childhood. .
.
.
i look out.
now i am grown.
that little girl inside -
she asks me how 
i could have let
myself be hurt this way
she asks me why i lied 
to myself
over and over and over,
in the hopes of acceptance
from a world that 
turns a blind eye
to the terror it 
perpetuates.
saying things like 
what did you wear?
did you drink too much?
well boys just cant 
help themselves. 
world. 
you make me 
sick. 
for i am only now seeing
all the abuse that was
inflicted on me -
what you call a
social justice warrior
is a hero to me. 
too many times
i thought it was all 
my fault and that i 
deserved it. 
after all -
i always gave it up. 
i didnt know.. they could have stopped. -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

text: after being told he would get a 24 hour notice before she would get released, he deemed it safe to let his mother-in-law help watch his son when he worked. see this helped me out too because at that time i had a two year old and an 8month old, and i watch the baby while my brother works. our whole family was against the idea of her family helping out at all until a custody order was in place, but after being told by two different sources that we would in fact get a 24 hour notice before she would be released, my brother deemed it safe to let his mother-in-law watch the baby while he worked. his mother-in-law bails her daughter out while watching the baby, and now they have custody because she is still the mother and no custody order is in place. the day this happened (july 16th, 2018) my brother did everything in his power to get his son back including calling the police and cys, nothing could be done. the only reason we even knew she was bailed out was i signed up for alerts from our county prison, to notify me of changes in the offenders status. which they notified me after she was already released. #domesticabuse #domesticviolence #emotionalabuse #abuse #domesticviolenceawareness #metoo #domesticviolencesurvivor #sociopath #narcissist #depressionandanxiety #narcissisticabusesurvivor #speakup #divorce #cptsd #emotionalabuse #abusiverelationships #victimblaming #abusiverelationship #abusedwomen #abusedmen #victimmentality #gaslighter #awareness #narcissisticabuse #gaslighting

text:
why did i leave ig? .
.
many people have been asking me so what did you do on your break from instagram. as if life in itself has to be done with instagram. it was my choice to separate to work on myself. now people keep asking me what does that mean which worries me. everyone says they need to work on themselves but then feel the need to ask others what â€œworking on themselves means.â€ itâ€™s up to you! whatever you feel you need to work on in your life the most than do it! eliminate all distractions, all excuses, all people, who arenâ€™t aligned with what you want or where you are going. personally through this time off iâ€™ve been able to become stronger emotionally, learn to accept myself while continuing to work on becoming better. i was very depressed and my mentality & actions werenâ€™t something i wanted to share at the moment with others. in fact i rarely had any human contact with anyone at all. yes i exercised, yes i ate better, yes i slept more, yes i prayed more ... but itâ€™s more of everything that i started to not do anymore that showed me my true growth as a person. i no longer have suicidal thoughts or self harm and iâ€™ve been dealing with that for the past 6 years on and off. but these past few months i took time to heal. and let me tell you healing is such a beautiful thing. .
.
i have kept all the messages of the people who wrote to me the day i left the gram and i actually read them a lot throughout my time away. itâ€™s amazing how words from people you donâ€™t even know can truly lift you up at times . so please donâ€™t underestimate the power of social media and using it to spread kindness. .
. 
i am happy, i am still working on myself but i value myself more than ever and it reflects completely with the people i choose to do life with. choose yourself first â¤ï¸
#empwr

text:
for many many years i have dedicated my career and life to empowering, encouraging and inspiring young women, girls and children. in light of recent disturbing news and also because i have never met more people in my entire life who want to be famous, i am focused on solutions to help educate parents and keep young women, girls and children safe. i will be creating new video content sharing tips on how to not be scammed or taken advantage of, the importance of having a positive support system around you, and so much more. i have already talked to some of my professional female friends in the entertainment industry and we will be sharing our stories and giving advice we wish we had known or were told when we were younger. i am also looking into how i can expand my mentoring programs so a team and i can reach more girls and children who are not being protected. i believe all violators should continue to be exposed and have to answer to their crimes, survivors should continue speaking up and get the help they need when they are ready, and i believe we need to be proactive because it takes a village! ğŸ’‹

text:

we must value the lives of black girls and women more than any superficial affinity.
.

text:
rape is rape!! no means no!!! stop means stop!!! if i said those words and you still did what you did without my consent, it's rape!! here's my story: 
#whyididntreport #metoo
i was raped 7 times. they were all different. the 1st 4 were when i was 12 to 16. by 3 different guys. i told my family..but they didn't believe me. neither did the police. i thought i deserved it.
i was raped a year ago by a person close to me.  he was younger than me. 
it happened 3 different times in 3 different months. i didn't tell anyone until last october. a month after it happened. again, nobody believed me. 
i thought it was my fault because i should've known better. i was older. everyone said it wasn't rape because i was older and i didn't come out pregnant. i didn't go to the doctor at all. for either times. i felt like i was an embarrassement to my family. like,"wow, you're 18,he was 14, that's not considered rape" i told him to stop.  that's another reason why i didn't say anything.
i told myself "i should've spoke up sooner. i just don't want to be judged." but i was. i was called names like, (excuse my language) slut and whore. 
it really hurt me. i got so depressed. i started to question god. i blamed it on him. it wasn't right. i thought he was punishing me. i couldn't eat, i couldn't sleep. i started to question everyone in my life...seeing if they would do the same thing or judge me for it. i pushed people away.. and learned to hide my feelings. i would fake smile and say i was fine. i eventually lost my faith...but i got it backâ¤ï¸ but i forgave those people who hurt me. it's still hard to this day. i regret just not doing anything to protect myself. i didn't fight back. he was stronger than me, for one thing. i just let him do it....i was scared. i just went about my day like normal. it was killing me on the inside. i'm 19, almost 20, and it still doesn't get any easier ğŸ˜¢

there's other people out there who have gone through this as well. the past doesn't define who we are, we just got to move forward.â˜ºï¸

text:
a woman who almost died through physical abuse
tricia st john is a tall chocolate woman with a kind smile and an overwhelming peace that permeates the room when she walks in. but also noticeable is the absence of her left forearm, two missing fingers from her right hand, multiple scars about her shoulders and cascading her neck, with a single three-inch long imprint lining her left templeâ€”disfigurements sustained by chop wounds from the wielding cutlass of an angry ex.

on april 2, 2004, st john, of south trinidad, almost met her death as she lay in a crouched position on her neighbourâ€™s front porch feeling each impact of the swinging blade.recounting the events of that horrifying evening, st john, who lived in port-of-spain at the time, had gone to her motherâ€™s san fernando property to visit her three sons who were being kept from her by their father.

he was subsequently convicted of attempted murder with grievous bodily harm and was sentenced in 2009 to 25 years imprisonment with ten strokes.
â€œwithin those fives years that he remained free, he could have finished me off at anytime or attack another woman. for victims this is a hellish ordeal and they are made to feel demeaned, appearing before magistrate after magistrate, telling the story over and over for years before an actual trial takes place.â€ but st john had a message to send to the authoritiesâ€”it is important that discrimination ends against people with disabilities.â€œ"i obtained these physical challenges through abuse. i did not do it to myself. and it does not matter how someone obtains a physical impairment. what matters is that we are still human beings who are still alive and want to live and live the best life that we can". #domesticviolence #abuse #mentalhealth #narcissisticabuse #sociopath #narcissist #domesticviolenceawareness #gaslighting #metoo #emotionalabuse #domesticabuse #mentalhealthawareness #sexualabuse #love #toxicpeople #verbalabuse #trauma #psychologicalabuse #domesticviolencesurvivor #narc #ptsd #divorce #stoptheviolence #suicideprevention #endthestigma #survivor #stopthestigma #narcawareness #suicidal #bhfyp

text:
with india s biggest director accused by his own assistant for sexual assault , the  few blind articles , his name being taken off as the co-producer from sonam kapoor s upcoming release suddenly make sense. . .
yes this might seem like an inappropriate time to bring this up , but i really feel like penning down my views. this is about the movie which broke all records and was the first indian movie to rake in a whooping 200 crores. yes three idiots. its much loved by the audience and labelled as a family movie but i could not digest the way rape was turned into a joke. the lewd jokes on a woman's breasts and the balatkar /chamatkar jokes literallymade me cringe . rape is not an issue which can be made fun of , in whatever situation but i was shocked at the way this scene was casually swept under the rug. no hue and cry , absolutely no mention of this disgusting five minutes scene by the pseudointellectuals makes you believe that the bigger your name in bollywood you will escape scott free from the repercussions.

ok coming back to the present looks like the shit just hit the ceiling ! hope more women come out and no abuser walks away from their crimes. in this particular scenario i really hope and pray that in this battle david again wins against goliath ! more power to each victim who takes a stand for themselves and speak to finally , we are with you â¤â¤â¤
#empoweringwomen #metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #mompresso #bollywood #rookiemums #likeforlikes #instamoms #speakup #takeastand

text:
as a kid
i heard
that every time you say
you don't believe in magic
a fairy dies.

then i realized
how many non-believers there were.

as a woman, i learned
that every time you say
you don't believe a rape,
a victim dies.

then i realized,
how many non-believers there are.

this world has prioritized 
abusers lies,
sought to ensure
that magic dies.

but somehow, 
both women
and fairies 
survive.

we sustain our own magic. 
we believe in ourselves.
we stay alive. ~
#endviolenceagainstwomen 
#believevictims

text:
â€œcreate of our lives a masterpiece.â€ joseph b. wirthlin from his talk titled the abundant life.
.
i canâ€™t stop looking at this collage my sister @the_librarycard made me, i love it! it goes along perfectly with that quote. it would be hard for anyone looking at this collage to know that at one point my husband iâ€™m still married to had packed up his things and moved out, asking for a divorce. the church i belong to had scheduled a meeting in which they would decide if i could even still be a member of their organization. i was standing at a point in my life where i got to chose if i was going to fight. was i going to fight for my family? for the church i loved and wanted to be a part of? typing this actually makes me teary eyed. that part of my life was so dang hard! #asoulsurvivorspiritual
.
i did chose to fight. but make no mistake about it, it was a lot of hard work, time and sacrifice!
.
but here is the awesome thing you guys...
.
we can actually create a masterpiece of our lives.
.
we get to do that! we get to do it every! single! day! make our lives a masterpiece! through the choices we make, the thoughts we think, the things we do, we get to create whatever we want out of our lives! you guys, if you want something, you have to create it. you have to make it happen. the life we want doesnâ€™t just come to us, wrapped in a present with a bow on top. we have to work to create it.
.
want to lose weight?
want to have a better marriage?
want to eat more veggies?
want to be more active? 
want to connect with your kids?
.
i have seen the difference in a life that i just let happen versus the one that i create and i am here to tell you that the one that takes work and sacrifice is hands down the one worth living.
.
i know, i know â€¦  iâ€™m like super late to the new year party but regardless, i am so pumped about the things i am creating for 2019! join me and letâ€™s create of our lives a masterpiece!

text:
campaigners say attempts to reduce domestic violence are not working because the number of women killed by men has remained steady for the last decade.

at least 139 women were murdered by a man last year â€“ including 21 killed in terrorist attacks â€“ according to the latest femicide census report.
one report said a victim had been stabbed 175 times, while other women were described as having been â€œhit 40 times with an axeâ€, â€œbludgeoned repeatedlyâ€ and â€œbattered virtually beyond all recognitionâ€.
three quarters of the victims last year were killed by someone they knew. almost half of the perpetrators were partners or former partners of their victim.

nearly two thirds of the women were killed at home, while more than half of the cases involving a former intimate partner happened during the first month of separation.

text:
mystikal could be walking out of jail as early as next week if everything goes to plan. according to tmz, a combination of funds from friends and a new record deal could lead to his release from caddo correctional center before his trial for first degree rape and second-degree kidnapping starts this spring.
mystikal's attorney, joel pearce, told the celebrity news outlet that his client's friends and family have been raising money for his $3 million bond but it was a newly-signed record deal that really helped him reach his goal.

according to tim yazbeck, another lawyer for the embattled rhymer, his new deal consist of him recording three unreleased albums. he's hoping to get an advance within days. mystikal's legal team is confident that the rapper can post bail and be released by the end of next week.

the ghetto fabulous artist has been behind bars since august 2017 after an unnamed woman accused both him and another man, averweone darnell holman, of raping her in may 2017. the alleged rape took place in october 2016. holman faces the same charges. a third person, a woman named tenichia monieck wafford, has also been charged with obstruction of justice in relation to the alleged assault for reportedly trying to persuade the woman to recant her story.
mystikal, whose real name is michael tyler, has denied all rape allegations against him and believes the entire situation was fueled by the #metoo movement that has exposed sexual misconduct by male executives and celebrities in the film and music industry.
mystikalâ€™s rape trial is expected to start in may.

this article from ucla lecturer and author kim elsesser shows that despite all the progress that's been made in recent years, we're still extremely distant from most men caring about equality - and when men care about their female workmates, it's mostly because they're afraid their sexual misdemeanours will be outed.
this misogynist attitude has to undergo radical change! in the place of the patriarchal system where women rely on men caring about their issues, we have to usher in an era where women have full and true control of their own lives and bodies, and will never be secondary to men in their occupations!

text:
someone asked me the other day about the #blackgirlmagicâœ¨ movement, and i wasn't entirely satisfied with my response at the time. so, i thought i would give myself a second chance. see, i need #blackwomen and #blackgirls and the #blackgirlmagicâœ¨ğŸ’« movement not only because society renders us invisible but by default those whom are invisible are also unprotected. and those whom are unprotected are easily excusable. there is no justice for raping a ghost, and there is no justice for killing ghosts either.i need #blackgirlmagic because of #niawilson, #rekiaboyd, #cyntoiabrown and #jazminebarnes and every unnamed black girl and woman that hasn't survived or named. i need it because #bringbackdcgirls and#mmiw. i need #blackgirlmagic because #survivingrkelly and #anitahill. i need #blackgirlmagic because #ayanapressley and #michelleobama are only the beginning. i need #blackgirlmagic because even #serenawilliams has to save her own life. i need #blackgirlmagic because #medicalracism and #educationalracism. i need #blackgirlmagic because it is 2019 and i am a first generation college graduate. because black women rank near the lowest paid per hour. i need #blackgirlmagic because when a brown boy sexually assaulted me no one cared until he assaulted a white girl. i need #blackgirlmagic because black girls are sexualized as an excuse for rape. when a 16 year old white boy sexually assaulted me i "wanted it." i was 8 years old. i need #blackgirlmagic because until the safety and protection of black women and girls becomes a priority, we will sacrifice the most. our dignity. our mental health. i need blackgirlmagic because merely surviving isn't living. we rise on the shoulders of our ancestors but we also rise with our sisters and mothers and daughters. #phenomenalwomen
#metoo #yesalldaughters #blacklivesmatter #blackwomen #believesurvivors #muterkelly #browngirl

text:
#metoo #timesup #muterkellyÂ  #godsaystimesupÂ  my next book, "the me too movement of the bible."Â understanding the will of god through the word of god and the me too movement

i had great hesitation in writing a book about the me too movement and the bible. in my hesitation, i begin to think that maybe a woman should write this book. in this book, i would be challenged to write about things that most preachers never preach or teach in their bible lessons. the sunday school lessons that are written never deal with the issue of sexual assault. most books that are written in the christian arena never deal with the issues that will be discussed in this book. i am about to write about something that if i came across in a movie, i would turn the movie off because i do not find such matters entertaining even in the world of make-believe movies.

but in dealing with these kinds of issues in real life you can't turn it off. you can't fast forward through the scenes that you don't like in real life. many who will read this book wish they could turn it off or fast forward through the pain. this book is a book written for all the silent victims of sexual harassment and sexual assault.Â  i pray that god will use this book to heal all the hurt and the shame that surrounds these heinous crimes.

coming spring 2019 ...take a look at dr. eaton's other books at 
amazon.com/author/revdrmichaeleaton

text:
my wings have been clipped for most of my life. however, today i'm no longer afraid of soaring!

growing up, fear was instilled in me non-stop.

about everything.

about being an illegal immigrant.
about not behaving or else.
about my motherâ€™s schizophrenia and how it was supposedly my fault.
so i was afraid i caused her maniac episodes.
about how as a teenager, i could get pregnant.
that was my welcome message to my first period.
i didnâ€™t understand what that really meant.
i was afraid of being a woman.
of being poor.
of being sent back to mexico by my family as punishment.
by immigration.
of driving.
of going to college.
of having a job.
i was the most naive teenager.

i literally cried myself to sleep as a young child because i was afraid of so many things.
my little self couldnâ€™t handle the pressure of the burden of fear i was given.
so i cried. all.the.time.
the kind of crying that hurts the soul.
the crying that with every tear drop i felt a deep pain in my lungs.
my crying was the silent kind.
i wasnâ€™t able to show it because i would get in trouble.
so i cried myself to sleep every night.

those many fears continued into my young adult life.
i was afraid of not succeeding.
then i became afraid of succeeding.
i was afraid i was not good enough.
i was afraid of being myself because i was never accepted to be me.
i was too bossy.
too outspoken.
too demanding.
too assertive.
afraid to let the fat go that had protected me from being too beautiful.
too attractive.
too powerful.
from being raped again.

no surprise, i married someone who kept the pattern going.
clipping my wings using religion and submission.
saying no to almost everything i wanted.
i did it anyway but the pain of not being supported hurt me deeply.
i was afraid to disappoint god and so i stayed much longer than i needed.

until i faced my fears, one by one.

text: there have been several moments of trauma in my life where i look back and feel guilty for how i responded. i feel the weight of shame that comes along with not overpowering my assailant, for not reporting it or for not pressing charges. a recent occurrence included a stranger who pinned me in a booth while he was assaulting me - me, a physically strong, loud, doesnâ€™t-put-up-with-crap woman. i was still wearing my church t-shirt and my church name-tag around my neck. a woman i taught with was on the other side of the restaurant with her husband who is a very well-known principal. i shut down, i didnâ€™t push him and i didnâ€™t scream. i froze. i hoped that the waitress could tell i was in distress, or the girl i taught with would know this man wasn't my husband and say something. i did my best to make it clear i was not interested and that he needed to leave me alone. when i look back at that situation, i often get angry that i didnâ€™t push him, scream at him and make a scene. i had nothing to be embarrassed about because i was doing nothing wrong, but yet i felt the pressure to not draw attention to myself. maybe someone would recognize my church name and find out the screaming lady at the restaurant actually worked for that church. i was afraid to cause a scene in front of a friend and her husband, the principal. i was afraid to cause disruption that would make all eyes turn on me. but a friend of mine reminded me that i am safe now and that in those moments i relied on survival patterns and traits that i picked up on while iâ€™ve endured trauma in the past. she didnâ€™t tell me to forgive myself for not knowing better, or forgive myself for giving away my power, or forgive myself for those survival patterns, but instead told me to thank my body for doing what i needed to get home safe. if you didnâ€™t respond to trauma the way you thought you would remember that youâ€™re not the one who should feel shame - you didnâ€™t do anything wrong - the trauma you faced is not a reflection of who you are. if youâ€™re recovering from trauma, i highly recommend seeking help from a trauma therapist. hear me say - you are not at fault and your trauma will not define you.

text:
calling all indigenous women of the americas!  native american/indigenous women are invited to join kanyon sayers-roods, aurora mamea, marge grow eppard & annita luchessi at the san francisco women's march.  kanyon sayers-roods will open the rally with a traditional ohlone welcome.  aurora mamea, annita luchessi & marge grow will share the stage to speak out for our missing & murdered indigenous women. (please share and tag yourself). meet at 10am on the right side of the stage to gather in prayer. 
women will be invited to stand in front of the stage as our sisters are speaking on the stage.

we will lead the march together behind a #mmiw banner after the rally at the civic center.

wear red. make a sign - some suggestions:

trauma to indigenous women = trauma to mother earth #mmiw

untold numbers of missing & murdered indigenous women #mmiw

we stand together #mmiw

not only #metoo also #mmiw

see you there ladies!

text:
calling all indigenous women of the americas!  native american/indigenous women are invited to join kanyon sayers-roods, aurora mamea, marge grow eppard & annita luchessi at the san francisco women's march.  kanyon sayers-roods will open the rally with a traditional ohlone welcome.  aurora mamea, annita luchessi & marge grow will share the stage to speak out for our missing & murdered indigenous women. (please share and tag yourself). meet at 10am on the right side of the stage to gather in prayer. 
women will be invited to stand in front of the stage as our sisters are speaking on the stage.

we will lead the march together behind a #mmiw banner after the rally at the civic center.

wear red. make a sign - some suggestions:

trauma to indigenous women = trauma to mother earth #mmiw

untold numbers of missing & murdered indigenous women #mmiw

we stand together #mmiw

not only #metoo also #mmiw

see you there ladies!
